node.text:
Pets & plants!

Let's first establish that this is a beautiful Philoden Gloriosum from @foliagedreams
Now lets talk about pets! As most of you know I got 2 cats, Poezel & Friendo. Friendo is my best friend, always close to me. Poezel on the other hand, sleeps all day & is mostly grumpy.

Most plants are toxic for pets. Yet I have my cats & plants in the same rooms, often Friendo hangs out in the plant room. At first I was afraid that they would bite the plants, or toss them over. Luckily, this never happens (sometimes they drink from a propagation jar but that's oke)

Do you have pets? If yes, what kind? And how do you handle plants & pets?

If your pet is tempted to bite your plant, use a water spray to keep them away. Or place tin foil on the soil as they don't like the feeling / sound of the foil. Or if you are really afraid you can place the most toxic plants on a high shelf. Google 'toxic plants' for a whole list!
